@host = http://localhost:3000
@apiKey = replace-with-your-API_KEY

### Health (no auth)
GET {{host}}/health

### Create a subscription — copy the returned "id" and "secret"
POST {{host}}/subscriptions
x-api-key: {{apiKey}}
content-type: application/json

{
  "target_url": "http://localhost:4000/hook",
  "event_type": "user.created"
}

### List subscriptions
GET {{host}}/subscriptions
x-api-key: {{apiKey}}

### Ingest an event (returns 202 immediately) — copy the returned "event_id"
POST {{host}}/events
x-api-key: {{apiKey}}
content-type: application/json
idempotency-key: evt-001

{
  "event_type": "user.created",
  "payload": { "user_id": 42, "email": "a@b.com" }
}

### Re-send the SAME idempotency-key => "duplicate": true, no new deliveries
POST {{host}}/events
x-api-key: {{apiKey}}
content-type: application/json
idempotency-key: evt-001

{
  "event_type": "user.created",
  "payload": { "user_id": 42, "email": "a@b.com" }
}

### Point a subscription at a FAILING endpoint to watch retries + dead-letter
# (create another subscription with target_url http://localhost:4000/hook?fail=1)

### See what happened to an event — paste the event_id from the ingest response
GET {{host}}/events/PASTE_EVENT_ID/deliveries
x-api-key: {{apiKey}}
